 \iint\limits_S {\sqrt{ \left(\frac{x^2}{a^4}+\frac{y^2}{b^4}+\frac{z^2}{c^4}\right)}}{dS} 
 S = \{(x,y,z)\in\mathbb{R}^3: \frac{x^2}{a^2} + \frac{y^2}{b^2} + \frac{z^2}{c^2}= 1\} 
{\bf n}
{\displaystyle {({x \over a^2}, {y \over b^2}, {z \over c^2}) \over \sqrt{ \left(\frac{x^2}{a^4}+\frac{y^2}{b^4}+\frac{z^2}{c^4}\right)}}}
{\bf F} = ({x \over a^2}, {y \over b^2}, {z \over c^2})
\int_S {\bf F} \cdot {\bf n}\,dS
